<subSubSection id="6FD5EB30C16E6640B6041205C237CCC9" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="comments">
<paragraph id="C920704C51E7CE639F99D317855AFCB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D63E9ACF17CA65A7A11836A6DAE685C" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName id="2AADB656883585332B7765BD6334025C" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar" authorityYear="2022" class="Aves" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea fluidifolia" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluidifolia">
<emphasis id="B7152D76B9884CB3A15875804CE8FF35" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Columnea fluidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from most 
<taxonomicName id="865AD3E6E9051D99B962A93E39B64365" class="Aves" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="08E531833CEF506CF44801C61B41D6D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Columnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of pendent elongate shoots and paired leaves that are both anisophyllous (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="681AD1A06A5D433A281FC526645E70D6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Columnea fluidifolia J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar A lateral view of mature flower B anisophyllous leaf pairs C isophyllous leaf pairs (base &amp; apex) and anisophyllous leaf pairs (middle) D immature berry E mature berry (A, B, D from J. L. Clark 16286 C, E from A. J. Perez &amp; F. Tobar sn). Photos A, B, D by J. L. Clark &amp; C, E by F. Tobar." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683752" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2A</figureCitation>
) and isophyllous (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="299C009A83423EE7B7FCFC1982199041" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Columnea fluidifolia J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar A lateral view of mature flower B anisophyllous leaf pairs C isophyllous leaf pairs (base &amp; apex) and anisophyllous leaf pairs (middle) D immature berry E mature berry (A, B, D from J. L. Clark 16286 C, E from A. J. Perez &amp; F. Tobar sn). Photos A, B, D by J. L. Clark &amp; C, E by F. Tobar." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683752" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2B</figureCitation>
). In addition, the shallowly bilabiate to tubular corolla and relatively large leaves (&gt; 4 cm long) are not typical for other 
<taxonomicName id="B0FFF172FF89DC33A60A21F4A9333739" class="Aves" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A6F4F62A23D4633EC2D38434E6FB9591" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Columnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with pendent elongate shoots. In contrast, most 
<taxonomicName id="9544A04C9213A0E66FBA56D2F19D43EE" class="Aves" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD3E5B858A115D93ADDFDEDC1A69C0EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Columnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with pendent elongate shoots have corollas that are deeply bilabiate and small leaves (&lt;4 cm long). 
<taxonomicName id="1A22A1410D1A6E4AECDDBDDCEEF1A25C" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar" authorityYear="2022" class="Aves" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea fluidifolia" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluidifolia">
<emphasis id="7352229928C18841BB1E9F56BBCA7697" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Columnea fluidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="29E1EEA38A43FCBE46E77E1685D384DC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. ceticeps" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ceticeps">
<emphasis id="012B2D33813E052BAF63DCB0D1139C4F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">C. ceticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The calyx lobes and corolla are orange in 
<taxonomicName id="473CB6FBCA974CEE3B7E1673BF2EF300" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. fluidifolia" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluidifolia">
<emphasis id="388B71D1798FFE18F613A1A7A304BC38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">C. fluidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AA55C1C29B6D604398C9DBB552DF2522" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Columnea fluidifolia J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar A lateral view of mature flower B anisophyllous leaf pairs C isophyllous leaf pairs (base &amp; apex) and anisophyllous leaf pairs (middle) D immature berry E mature berry (A, B, D from J. L. Clark 16286 C, E from A. J. Perez &amp; F. Tobar sn). Photos A, B, D by J. L. Clark &amp; C, E by F. Tobar." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683752" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2</figureCitation>
). In contrast, the calyx lobes are green, and the corolla is bright orange in 
<taxonomicName id="8843939FBEE8465C6EE69FD975223304" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. ceticeps" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ceticeps">
<emphasis id="690855B3703D6A99F740599108B7063A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">C. ceticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6A1918F30973D9ABE06EC88266536C6F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Columnea ceticeps J. L. Clark &amp; J. F. Sm. A mature flower B pendent shoot C deeply bilabiate corolla D calyx lobes (A-D from J. L. Clark 12950 D photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683754" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">4</figureCitation>
). The corolla tube in 
<taxonomicName id="05CA478C722117E1CEBB4E27F46BA9F2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. fluidifolia" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluidifolia">
<emphasis id="F02769B0E7BE7AA417817BEE32DD8838" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">C. fluidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nearly tubular without the presence of a bilabiate limb (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9BEC44D17E7DF716BB7C01F04BD93909" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Columnea fluidifolia J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar A lateral view of mature flower B anisophyllous leaf pairs C isophyllous leaf pairs (base &amp; apex) and anisophyllous leaf pairs (middle) D immature berry E mature berry (A, B, D from J. L. Clark 16286 C, E from A. J. Perez &amp; F. Tobar sn). Photos A, B, D by J. L. Clark &amp; C, E by F. Tobar." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683752" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CBE4393AB06E17C44C4EFAD8FC9D3D98" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Columnea fluidifolia J. L. Clark &amp; F. Tobar A pendent shoot B lateral view of flower C bilobed dorsal nectary gland and ovary D mature calyx with style E stomatomorphic stigma F corolla opened featuring mature anthers G mature corolla. Illustration by M. J. Gavilanes." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683753" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">3</figureCitation>
). In contrast, the corolla tube in 
<taxonomicName id="63C6922D00CF9E5C1A8EC5EE62E2C7F3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="C." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. ceticeps" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ceticeps">
<emphasis id="B182A1FDA71ECC918A3BDDEC4DAB64C0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">C. ceticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deeply bilabiate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEB991D17CE4CBB6F343DA093E6F97AB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Columnea ceticeps J. L. Clark &amp; J. F. Sm. A mature flower B pendent shoot C deeply bilabiate corolla D calyx lobes (A-D from J. L. Clark 12950 D photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.196.79673.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683754" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
